1.00	Viper's_grass	Scorzonera hispanica	Scorzonera hispanica, black salsify or Spanish salsify, also known as black oyster plant, serpent root, viper's herb, viper's grass or simply Scorzonera, is a perennial member of the genus Scorzonera in the sunflower family , cultivated as a root vegetable in the same way as some of the members of the salsify genus Tragopogon, also in the sunflower family.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/11/Schorseneer_plant_Scorzonera_hispanica.jpg/220px-Schorseneer_plant_Scorzonera_hispanica.jpg
